<a href="#video-link" data-video-id="vlyt0h" data-video-descrip="It's a relatively short level, as if that makes up for anything in it. It's very easy to fall off (being a Floating Continent-type level), has some mildly annoying enemies (the large ones have a somewhat wide-range kick, and the smaller ones throw banana bunch-like projectiles without any sound cues), and to get everything, you're gonna need to pull off some Guide Dang It!-y Super Charge maneuvers. Route is outlined here. Spyro even lampshades this by complaining to the dragon you find doing this route that he &amp;quot;could have found an easier spot to get stuck.&amp;quot;" data-video-title="Tree Tops" data-video-url="https://d1w6li7s85ibls.cloudfront.net/qvbr/vlyt0h_640x360p_qvbr.mp4" data-video-thumbnail="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/vlyt0h.jpg" data-video-trope="Main/ThatOneLevel" data-video-tropename="That One Level" data-video-approval="APPROVED" data-video-troper-rating="" data-video-average-rating="" data-video-rating-count="" data-video-media-sources="VideoGame/SpyroTheDragon1998" class="video-launch-link video-overlay-link video-background-image lazy-image" data-src="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/vlyt0h.jpg">
